    "created": "2025-08-17T05:44:51.345Z",
    "updated": "2025-08-17T05:44:51.345Z",
    "status": "PB"
  }
},
{
  "model": "blog.post",
  "pk": 6,
  "fields": {
    "title": "what is machine learning",
    "slug": "what-is-machine-learning",
    "author": 1,
    "body": "Machine learning is a subset of artificial intelligence that enables systems to learn from data and improve their performance on a specific task without being explicitly programmed. Essentially, it allows computers to learn from experience by analyzing data and identifying patterns, rather than relying on pre-defined rules.",
    "publish": "2025-08-17T05:46:00Z",
    "created": "2025-08-17T05:46:06.768Z",
    "updated": "2025-08-17T05:46:06.768Z",
    "status": "PB"
  }
},
{
  "model": "blog.post",
  "pk": 7,
  "fields": {
    "title": "What is python",
    "slug": "what-is-python",
    "author": 1,
    "body": "Python is a high-level, general-purpose programming language known for its readability and simplicity. It was created by Guido van Rossum and first released in 1991.",
    "publish": "2025-08-17T05:46:17Z",
